Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs` to hook platform-native callbacks:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android `OnPause` = lost focus (maps to `Deactivated`); `OnStop` = fully backgrounded (maps to `Stopped`)
- iOS `DidEnterBackground` maps to the `Stopped` window event
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need platform-specific APIs, override `OnStopped()` on a `Window` subclass — it fires on all platforms when the app backgrounds:

```csharp
protected override void OnStopped()
{
    base.OnStopped();
    Preferences.Set("draft", _vm.Draft);
}
```
